analysisPopulations.name: Randomized population
analysisPopulations.text: All patients who are randomly assigned a treatment arm
analysisPopulations.label: Randomized
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All patients who are randomly assigned a treatment arm

analysisPopulations.name: Modified intent-to-treat population
analysisPopulations.text: All randomly assigned participants who are exposed to at least 1 dose of study drug.
analysisPopulations.label: mITT
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All randomly assigned participants who are exposed to at least 1 dose of study drug.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Efficacy analysis set
analysisPopulations.text: Data obtained during Study Period II and III from mITT, excluding patients discontinuing study drug due to inadvertent enrollment and data after initiating rescue antihyperglycemic medication or discontinuation of study drug (last dose date + 7 days).
analysisPopulations.label: EAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Data obtained during Study Period II and III from mITT, excluding patients discontinuing study drug due to inadvertent enrollment and data after initiating rescue antihyperglycemic medication or discontinuation of study drug (last dose date + 7 days).
analysisPopulations.criteria: mITT AND not discontinued due to inadvertent enrollment AND data prior to rescue/discontinuation

analysisPopulations.name: Full analysis set
analysisPopulations.text: Data obtained during Study Period II and III from mITT, excluding patients discontinuing study drug due to inadvertent enrollment, regardless of adherence to study drug or initiation of rescue antihyperglycemic medication.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Data obtained during Study Period II and III from mITT, excluding patients discontinuing study drug due to inadvertent enrollment, regardless of adherence to study drug or initiation of rescue antihyperglycemic medication.
analysisPopulations.criteria: mITT AND not discontinued due to inadvertent enrollment

analysisPopulations.name: Safety analysis set
analysisPopulations.text: Data obtained during Study Period II, III, and IV from mITT, regardless of adherence to study drug or initiation of new antihyperglycemic medication.
analysisPopulations.label: SS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Data obtained during Study Period II, III, and IV from mITT, regardless of adherence to study drug or initiation of new antihyperglycemic medication.
